When%20Nadella%20first%20took%20over%2C%20one%20of%20his%20first%20acts%20was%20to%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20he%20wanted%20Microsoft%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnadella-just-rejected-ballmers-vision-2014-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estop%20being%20a%20%26quot%3Bdevices%20and%20services%26quot%3B%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20to%20pivot%20to%20cloud%20computing%20and%20open-source%20software%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20its%20acquisition%20of%20Nokia%20was%20only%20finalized%20that%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Nadella's%20predecessor%2C%20Steve%20Ballmer%2C%20orchestrated%20the%20deal.%20It%20was%20a%20move%20he%20tried%20to%20dissuade%20Ballmer%20from%20following%2C%20Nadella%20said%20in%20his%202017%20book%20%26quot%3BHit%20Refresh.%26quot%3B%20So%2C%20by%202016%2C%20Microsoft%20ditched%20its%20mobile%20business%20and%20sold%20the%20Nokia%20phone%20line%20to%20follow%20Nadella's%20new%20vision%20for%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella's%20approach%20to%20transformation%20was%20not%20only%20about%20strategy%20but%20also%20about%20mindset.%20As%20he%20expressed%20in%20his%20book%2C%20Nadella%20thinks%2C%20%26quot%3BEvery%20person%2C%20organization%2C%20and%20even%20society%20reaches%20a%20point%20at%20which%20they%20owe%20it%20to%20themselves%20to%20hit%20refresh%20%E2%80%94%20to%20reenergize%2C%20renew%2C%20reframe%2C%20and%20rethink%20their%20purpose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20two%20years%2C%20Microsoft%20pushed%20down%20on%20building%20up%20its%20market%20share%20in%20cloud%20computing%20and%20became%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20players%2C%20second%20only%20to%20Amazon.%20Then%20came%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-buys-github-for-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%247.5%20billion%20acquisition%20of%20GitHub%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20platform%20where%20developers%20create%20and%20share%20code.%20This%20cemented%20Nadella's%20vision%20to%20build%20up%20its%20open-source%20software%20offering%2C%20solidifying%20Nadella's%20vision%20to%20boost%20Microsoft's%20open-source%20software%20offerings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202019%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatya-nadella-bill-gates-microsoft-concern-google-rivals-ai-emails-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20had%20become%20%26quot%3Bvery%2C%20very%20worried%26quot%3B%20about%20Google's%20progress%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20artificial%20intelligence.%20So%20much%20so%20that%20CTO%20Kevin%20Scott%20emailed%20Nadella%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates-still-pulling-strings-microsoft-ai-copilot-chatgpt-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBill%20Gates%3C%2Fa%3E%20telling%20them%20that%20Google's%20AI-powered%20%26quot%3Bauto-complete%20in%20Gmail%26quot%3B%20was%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20scarily%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20emails%2C%20with%20the%20subject%20line%20%26quot%3BThoughts%20on%20OpenAI%2C%26quot%3B%20might%20have%20motivated%20Microsoft%20to%20seek%20partnerships%20to%20bolster%20its%20own%20AI%20efforts.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20Microsoft%20made%20an%20initial%20%241%20billion%20investment%20in%20OpenAI.%20Its%20reported%20total%20investment%20into%20the%20ChatGPT%20maker%20has%20now%20hit%20%2413%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-openai-antitrust-watchdog-partnership-merger-probe-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epartnered%20with%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20infuse%20its%20technology%20into%20its%20own%20products%2C%20including%20its%20search%20engine%20Bing%20and%20GitHub%20Copilot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20isn't%20afraid%20to%20embrace%20change%2C%20so%20he%20pulls%20the%20trigger%20if%20the%20business%20requires%20outside%20expertise.%20In%20March%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-hired-inflection-team-amid-board-concerns-about-openai-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20announced%20that%20it%20tapped%20DeepMind%20and%20Inflection%20AI%20cofounder%20Mustafa%20Suleyman%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20lead%20its%20new%20AI%20organization.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bacqui-hire%26quot%3B%20deal%2C%20most%20of%20Inflection's%20workforce%20also%20joined%20Microsoft%2C%20which%20paid%20the%20company%20%24650%20million%20to%20license%20its%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuleyman%20is%20overseeing%20the%20building%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-training-ai-model-rivals-openais-gpt-4-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein-house%20AI%20model%20called%20MAI-1%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20dataset%20that%20includes%20text%20from%20ChatGPT%20and%20outside%20sources%20like%20public%20information%20on%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella's%20transformation%20of%20Microsoft%20involved%20changing%20its%20culture%20from%20%26quot%3Bknow-it-alls%20to%20learn-it-alls.%26quot%3B%20Speaking%20at%20a%20session%20as%20part%20of%20the%202022%20Wharton%20Future%20of%20Work%20Conference%2C%20Nadella%20said%20this%20learning%20culture%20is%20about%20a%20%26quot%3Bcontinuous%20process%20of%20renewal%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20credits%20psychologist%20Carol%20Dweck's%20growth%20mindset%20theory%20with%20inspiring%20him%20to%20create%20cultural%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20two%20students%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20them%20has%20more%20innate%20capability%2C%20and%20the%20other%20has%20less.%20The%20person%20who%20has%20less%20but%20is%20a%20learn-it-all%20will%20ultimately%20%5Bbecome%5D%20better.%20That%20applies%20to%20CEOs%2C%20and%20that%20applies%20to%20companies.%20I%20think%20it%20has%20been%20a%20helpful%20cultural%20metaphor%20for%20us%20to%20say%20that%20you%20can't%20act%20like%20a%20know-it-all%3B%20you%20have%20to%20be%20a%20learn-it-all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Microsoft%20