26quot%3Brisky%26quot%3B%20for%20Russia's%20air%20force%2C%20especially%20if%20it%20wants%20to%20maintain%20its%20force%20for%20a%20future%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a0c3531d-d04a-48ed-a956-2470e68e6e89%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia's%20comfortable%20losing%20what%20it's%20losing%20now%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECurtis%20said%20Russia%20is%20using%20its%20most%20advanced%20assets%20in%20ways%20that%20keep%20them%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20safe%2C%26quot%3B%20like%20launching%20long-range%20attacks%20from%20inside%20Russia.%20There's%20%26quot%3Beffectively%20no%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Layton%20said%20Russia%20may%20be%20motivated%20by%20its%20own%20weapons%20industry%2C%20which%20has%20ramped%20up%20but%20still%20faces%20challenges.%20%26quot%3BAny%20losses%20impact%20possible%20future%20export%20sales%20as%20Russian%20aircraft%20now%20appear%20less%20capable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Some%20experts%20have%20suggested%20this%20as%20a%20possible%20reason%20for%20keeping%20the%20Su-57%20out%20of%20the%20fight%2C%20especially%20given%20Russia's%20significant%20activity%20in%20foreign%20arms%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Four%20Sukhoi%20Su-57%20fighter%20jets%20in%20the%20air%20against%20a%20grey%20sky.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a0d70480d4d5da13d693d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESukhoi%20Su-57%20fighter%20jets%20perform%20near%20Moscow%2C%20Russia%2C%20in%20August%202019.%3Cp%3ESputnik%2FAleksey%20Nikolskyi%2FKremlin%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGeorge%20Barros%2C%20a%20Russia%20analyst%20at%20the%20US-based%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%20think%20tank%20that%20has%20been%20closely%20tracking%20the%20war%2C%20said%20Russia%20only%20has%20a%20small%20number%20of%20many%20of%20its%20most%20advanced%20aircraft%2C%20which%20means%20they%